Key Match Events: David Miller scored an unbeaten 59 to lead South Africa to victory.
Tristan Stubbs contributed 33 runs in a crucial partnership with Miller.
Vivian Kingma took 2 wickets for 12 runs, including key dismissals in the powerplay.
Anrich Nortje and Marco Jansen each took 2 wickets, contributing to Netherlands' low score.
Ottneil Baartman had impressive bowling figures of 4 for 11.
Post-Match Reflections: David Miller expressed relief and satisfaction at finishing the game and overcoming past defeats against Netherlands.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in New York as part of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup.
South Africa ended their losing streak against Netherlands in ICC tournaments.
